'''Acceptation''', ''<code>[[noun (part of speech)|noun]]</code>''

<ol>
<li>[[Acceptance]]; reception; favorable reception or regard; state of being [[acceptable]]. [Obs.]

<code>This is saying worthy of all ''acceptation''. ''[[1 Tim. i. 15 (source)|1 Tim. i. 15]].''</code>

<code>Some things ... are notwithstanding of so great dignity and ''acceptation'' with God. ''[[Hooker (source)|Hooker]].''</code>

<li> The meaning in which a word or expression is [[understood]], or generally received; as, term is to be used according to its usual ''acceptation''.

<code>My words, in common ''acceptation'', Could never give this provocation. ''[[Gay (source)|Gay]].''</code>
</ol>